                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1230: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-23T14:00:00-03:00"
                            >June 23, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. This Embassy’s despatch No. 3600 dated May 20.<note n="64" xml:id="d567fn64"
                        >Not printed.</note> Yesterday, at the weekly diplomatic audience, the
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs again pointed out that the dangerous tension which
                    existed between Bolivia and Paraguay was increasing. He is of the opinion that
                    measures should be taken to induce Bolivia and Paraguay to accept the double
                    arbitration set forth in that despatch. While the Minister did not say so,
                    Brazil is evidently prepared to assume some interested part in the [proposed?]
                    reconciliation which it declined to do at the time of the appointment of the
                    neutral committee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
